248
00:23:59,760 --> 00:24:02,600
Okay. So first of all, you've 
shared all these types of crisis,  

249
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:06,720
I think it might be helpful to do a quick 
taxonomy of the types of crisis founders  

250
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:14,520
face. You shared regulation changes, competitors 
coming at you, investors not wanting to invest.

251
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:22,920
So two types of, abstractly, two types of crisis. 
One is that I would call that a cash crisis. So  

252
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:34,560
all of a sudden your cash program or plan is being 
jeopardized, for losing a customer, disappearing  

253
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:44,000
investor, not meeting your expectation, dramatic 
price change in the market and so forth. And the  

254
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:52,160
other one is lose of product market fit. So all of 
a sudden whatever you have is irrelevant anymore  

255
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:56,960
and you actually need to go back to square one.
For the first type of crisis, if this is a cash  

256
00:24:56,960 --> 00:25:02,040
crisis, then what you really need to 
ask yourself, and in any type crisis,  

257
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:11,560
first of all is what is actually being impacted? 
Is that my run rate, is that my product, is that  

258
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:22,560
my revenue stream? If I'm still relevant?
With Order.chat, we were irrelevant,  

259
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:29,040
that's it. And so the first thing that you 
need to do is what is really being impacted?  

260
00:25:29,040 --> 00:25:35,720
And then the second thing is how long it's 
going to last? Is that a temporary thing?  

261
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:46,160
Is that forever? Is that the new future? And 
then you ask yourself, okay, so how much run  

262
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:54,120
rate do I have? And you re-plan accordingly.
And I'll give you some examples, and this is  

263
00:25:54,120 --> 00:26:05,160
really important, because let's say that you're 
a company that we have $5 million of revenues a  

264
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:15,960
year, say 400,000 per month, and your burn rate, 
your net burn rate is 200,000. So you actually at  

265
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:20,080
the end of the year, in order to run for a year, 
you need about two and a half million dollars to  

266
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:28,400
run. If you lose half of the revenues, and 
you only had two and a half million in the  

267
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:35,960
bank, you now have six month to run. 
So obviously you need to re-adapt. 

268
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:40,000
Now, one of the things that you might say to 
yourself, "I'm going to remain on the same  

269
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:46,920
course and I'm going to deal with the crisis in 
five month from now." Or you can basically say,  

270
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:55,320
"No, I'm going to change my expense to adjust 
to the current revenue stream that I have and  

271
00:26:55,320 --> 00:27:00,880
still have 12 month of run rate."
Whatever you are going to decide,  

272
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:07,640
you are going to decide, you need to decide today, 
right now. And the reason is very simple, if you  

273
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:15,000
want to reduce the burn, the expenses in order to 
extend the run rate, if you wait two more month,  

274
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:19,200
then it's going to become nearly impossible to 
do. If you wait six more month, then obviously  

275
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:27,480
this is impossible to do. So the longer that 
you wait, you actually lose options. The only  

276
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:34,920
ability to choose is today. This is one of the 
most challenging part of a crisis. You actually  

277
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:42,920
need to make a decision rapidly, like today.
There are few reasons to that. Number one is  

278
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:50,560
that if you don't then you might lose options. 
Number two, and this is about communicating  

279
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:57,880
within the organization that decision. Look, if 
there is a crisis everyone knows, everyone knows,  

280
00:27:57,880 --> 00:28:03,120
and you don't do anything about it, this is not 
a good practice. Now you might want to decide,  

281
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:10,960
no, we're going to keep on running full steam 
